  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\"\u0d85\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0dbd\u0dba \u0d85\u0dc0\u0dc3\u0db1\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dc4\u0dd0,\u0d89\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0da7 \u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dcf\"",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "\"The struggle is not over, it continues\"",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "On this occasion when Parliament has elected Ranil Wickremesinghe for the post of President with a majority of 52 votes, activists held a press conference at Gotagogama struggle ground in Galle mouth.",
        "They told the media that the struggle is not over and will continue.",
        "There, Father Jivantha Peiris said that the struggle was a struggle that achieved public victories and sacrificed lives. He stated that the second aim of the struggle is the resignation of Ranil Wickremesinghe.",
        "Sugathananda Thero of Tampitiya said that Ranil Wickramasinghe was appointed as anti-democratic.",
        "\"Who is behind Ranil? The people of this country did not ask for the appointment of Ranil. This appointment was due to other ambitions,\" he said.",
        "Lawyer Nuwan Bopage said that the people were oppressed by the existing government. He said that the Parliament is responsible for this, and from this week there will be an era when the people will have to take to the streets again.",
        "Eranga Gunasekara, the national organizer of the Socialist Youth Union, said, \"It was not Ranil who became the president, but Gotabaya, the ghosts of Gotabaya.\"",
        "The convener of the Inter-University Student Council, Wasantha Mudalige, also said: \"Even when the struggle has succeeded in driving out Gotabhaya, there is a conspiracy in the parliament. The members of Pohottuve made Ranil president to cover up their fraud and become ministers.\"",
        "He said that Ranil Wickremesinghe was brought to the presidency because of \"Rajapaksha's fraud\", and he will continue the struggle to oust Wickremesinghe from office.",
        "Currently, Colombo Fort Magistrate Thilina Gamage has issued an order today (July 20) preventing any party from entering the area 50 meters from the Galle mouthpiece Bandaranaike statue.",
        "It is said that the Magistrate took this step after considering a request made by the Fort Police to the court saying that they had received information that there were plans to damage the statue."
      ],
